# No Build / Install Unless Instructed

Do **not** run any of the following unless the user **explicitly requests it in the current message**:

- `npm install` / `npm ci`
- `npm run build` / `npm run start` / `npm run serve` / `npm run dev`
- `yarn install` / `pnpm install`
- Docusaurus build or dev server commands
- `composer install` / `composer update` (unless user asked to install dependencies)

## Allowed without explicit request

- Editing Markdown in `V2.0/docs/`
- Editing `V2.0/docs-site/sidebars.js` or `docusaurus.config.js`
- Reading files and writing documentation content
- **Running tests:** `./vendor/bin/pest`, `php artisan test`, Vitest on changed files, Playwright when user asked to verify flows
- Lint/format on changed files when verifying quality (Pint, PHPStan, ESLint)

## When the user asks to build

Only then run install/build, and prefer `npm install` or `composer install` only if dependencies are missing.

## Quality still required without build

Even when not building frontend bundles, code must be tested (see `.cursor/rules/testing-and-quality.mdc`) and must not ship broken flows or server errors.
